		{
			dependencies: [
				"0B38F16DB41E2CB2"
				"6F1701A9FE54115B"
			]
			description: [
				"The &bME Controller&r is what powers your entire Network. A Controller can be comprised of &6one or more blocks&r, as long as they fit &6within the rules specified in the in-game guide&r. "
				""
				"Regardless, each block face of the Controller &bprovides 32 Channels&r for cables to use."
				""
				"&6Right-clicking&r the Controller will provide a &bsummary&r of connected Devices, and power information."
				""
				"&6Power&r can be provided to the Network directly to the Controller, or by use of an &6Energy Acceptor&r."
			]
			hide_dependency_lines: true
			id: "47C777F331C82EF4"
			rewards: [{
				id: "025F38877A32DE7E"
				type: "xp"
				xp: 20
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "675C1CD55CBB49D9"
				item: "ae2:controller"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: 1.0d
			y: -4.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: [
				"6CEEC5D9627C306E"
				"5A55E22C6CFF8ADA"
			]
			description: [
				"&bNetwork Channels&r are a complex mechanic in AE2 that anyone building an ME Network will need to keep track of."
				"Note that &6the AE2 in-game guide has a much better explanation&r of Channels than what's explained here, so you may want to look at that."
				""
				"Each machine or block that interacts with the ME Network is considered a \"&bDevice&r\", and almost all Devices will &6consume a channel&r on the Network."
				""
				"The ME Controller &6provides the Network with channels&r on each face, and ME Cables simply &6connect Devices to the Network&r using Channels. The length of the cable being used does not matter."
				""
				"If a Network &bexceeds its channel limit&r on a cable, &6no new Devices&r may be added. This can be seen in Jade when it shows \"Device Missing Channel\"."
				""
				"More info on specific components can be found in each component's &6summary tooltips, in the following quests, and in the in-game guide.&r"
			]
			id: "0B38F16DB41E2CB2"
			min_width: 300
			rewards: [{
				id: "57000B3B2529E932"
				type: "xp"
				xp: 20
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "42A65AE754998038"
				title: "Understanding Channels"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			x: -0.5d
			y: -3.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: [
				"50A92B36E634CEDF"
				"04AE773451C0EE14"
				"47C777F331C82EF4"
				"79B5CC5DBA7F77C2"
				"347D7F4667EFD64A"
			]
			description: [
				"By putting these five components together in the world, you can &bcreate your first ME Network&r. While it is possible to set up a basic network without using cables, it would be best to &6use cables&r to provide room for expansion later on."
				""
				"You'll also need to &bprovide the Controller with power&r."
				""
				"Note that the ME Network &6does not care about cable distance&r, so you can have cables stretch across your base if you want."
				""
				"The Network can be built in &6any way you want&r, so the next two pages will have some examples."
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"{image:srsp:textures/ftbquests/controller-1.png width:240 height:135 align:center}"
				""
				"This setup shows how a Network could be set up &6without using ME Cables&r, except for the Terminal. This is &cnot recommended&r, however, as you will quickly run into channel bottlenecks."
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"{image:srsp:textures/ftbquests/controller-2.png width:240 height:135 align:center}"
				""
				"This setup is ideal for starting out. Using a &6Dense Cable&r to route channels to the Terminal &7(stepped down to a normal cable)&r and to the Drive allows you to &bexpand your network&r much further in the future."
			]
			id: "7C25D84F795B1729"
			min_width: 250
			rewards: [{
				id: "391545704E7C52DE"
				type: "xp"
				xp: 20
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "21B46384A1A25D19"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			title: "Putting it All Together"
			x: 0.0d
			y: -6.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["7C25D84F795B1729"]
			description: [
				"Now that you've built a Network, it's time to &6expand it&r."
				""
				"You can do so by &6adding more&r storage cells and drives, or by looking to the &bother questlines&r for AE2."
				""
